#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:1
msgid "Votes and Ranking"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:3
msgid "Posts"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:5
msgid ""
"Lemmy uses a voting system to sort post listings. On the left side of each "
"post there are _up_ and _down_ arrows, which let you _upvote_ or _downvote_ "
"it. You can upvote posts that you like so that more users will see them, or "
"downvote posts so that they are less likely to be seen. Each post receives a "
"score which is the number of upvotes minus the number of downvotes."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:7
msgid "Sorting Posts"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:9
msgid ""
"When browsing the front page or a community, you can choose between the "
"following sort types for posts:"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:11 src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:35
msgid "Sort"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:11 src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:35
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:13
msgid "Active (default)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:13
msgid ""
"Calculates a rank based on the score and time of the latest comment, with "
"decay over time"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:14
msgid "Hot"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:14
msgid "Like active, but uses time when the post was published"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:15
msgid "Scaled"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:15
msgid "Like hot, but gives a boost to less active communities"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:16
msgid "Controversial"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:16
msgid "Shows most controversial posts (many up and downvotes)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:17 src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:39
msgid "New"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:17
msgid "Shows most recent posts first"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:18 src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:40
msgid "Old"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:18
msgid "Shows oldest posts first"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:19
msgid "Most Comments"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:19
msgid "Shows posts with highest number of comments first"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:20
msgid "New Comments"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:20
msgid ""
"Bumps posts to the top when they are created or receive a new reply, "
"analogous to the sorting of traditional forums"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:21
msgid "Top Day"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:21
msgid "Highest scoring posts during the last 24 hours"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:22
msgid "Top Week"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:22
msgid "Highest scoring posts during the last 7 days"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:23
msgid "Top Month"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:23
msgid "Highest scoring posts during the last 30 days"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:24
msgid "Top Year"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:24
msgid "Highest scoring posts during the last 12 months"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:25
msgid "Top All Time"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:25
msgid "Highest scoring posts of all time"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:27
msgid "Comments"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:29
msgid ""
"Comments are by default arranged in a hierarchy which shows at a glance who "
"it is replying to. Top-level comments which reply directly to a post are on "
"the very left, not indented at all. Comments that are responding to top-"
"level comments are indented one level and each further level of indentation "
"means that the comment is deeper in the conversation. With this layout, it "
"is always easy to see the context for a given comment, by simply scrolling "
"up to the next comment which is indented one level less."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:31
msgid "Sorting Comments"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:33
msgid ""
"Comments can be sorted in the following ways. These all keep the indentation "
"intact, so only replies to the same parent are shuffled around."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:37
msgid "Hot (default)"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:37
msgid "Equivalent to the _Hot_ sort for posts"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:38
msgid "Top"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:38
msgid "Shows comments with highest score first"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:39
msgid "Shows most recent comments first"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:40
msgid "Shows oldest comments first"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:42
msgid ""
"Additionally there is a sort option **Chat**. This eliminates the hierarchy, "
"and puts all comments on the top level, with newest comments shown at the "
"top. It is useful to see new replies at any point in the conversation, but "
"makes it difficult to see the context."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:44
msgid ""
"The ranking algorithm is described in detail [here](../contributors/07-"
"ranking-algo.md)."
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:46
msgid "Vote Privacy"
msgstr ""

#: src/users/03-votes-and-ranking.md:48
msgid ""
"Lemmy attempts to limit the visibility of votes to protect user privacy. But "
"due to the way Lemmy works, votes cannot be completely private. Instance "
"admins can see the names of everyone who voted on a given post or comment, "
"and community moderators can see the names for the communities they "
"moderate. This helps to fight against vote manipulation. Additionally, "
"individual votes are federated over ActivityPub together with the "
"corresponding username. This means that other federated platforms can freely "
"choose how to display vote information, even going as far as publicly "
"displaying individual votes."
msgstr ""
